    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-10-22T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-10-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="267"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d267">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">G/PM Files, Lot 68 D 349</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the <gloss type="from">Special Assistant</gloss>
                        to the Secretary of State</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Arneson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-10-22">October 22,
                            1951</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Memorandum for the Secretary</hi>
                </p>
                <p rend="flushleft">Subject: Second Soviet Atomic Explosion in Current Test
                    Series</p>
                <p>In discussing with the President how we should play the second recent Soviet
                    explosion you will want to have the following points in mind: <list>
                        <label>1.</label>
                        <item>Extraordinary steps are being taken to try to keep this event from
                            leaking.</item>
                        <label>2.</label>
                        <item>We do not wish to say anything unless we are forced to.</item>
                        <label>3.</label>
                        <item>In the event that the “leak” comes from the Kremlin we should be
                            prepared to acknowledge that we have been aware of the second
                            shot.</item>
                        <pb facs="0798" n="782" xml:id="pg_782"/>
                        <label>4.</label>
                        <item>If our hand is forced, the story should be played down both in terms
                            of what is said and who says it. The attached draft to be used, if
                            necessary, by the <gloss target="#t_AEC1">AEC</gloss> is designed to
                            accomplish this.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <p>The foregoing points are concurred in by Messrs. Matthews, Nitze,<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d267fn1">Paul H. Nitze, Director of the Policy Planning
                        Staff.</note> Bonbright,<note n="2" xml:id="d267fn2">James C. H. Bonbright,
                        Deputy Assistant Secretary of State for European Affairs.</note> and
                        Armstrong.<note n="3" xml:id="d267fn3">W. Park Armstrong, Jr., Special
                        Assistant to the Secretary of State for Intelligence.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">R. Gordon Arneson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <frus:attachment>
                    <opener>
                        <seg rendition="#center">[Annex]</seg>
                    </opener>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">Draft Statement Prepared by the <gloss type="from">Special
                                Assistant</gloss> to the Secretary of State</hi> (<persName
                            type="to">
                            <hi rend="italic">Arneson</hi>
                        </persName>)</head>
                    <opener>
                        <seg rendition="#left">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                        </seg>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                            </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-10-22">October 22,
                                1951</date>.]</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>A second atomic explosion in the current Soviet test series has recently
                        occurred. Further tests may be expected as a normal adjunct to the Soviet
                        atomic weapons program.</p>
                </frus:attachment>
            </div>
